# Project Rules

## Data Fetching
- Always fetch community data from the backend API
- Never use hardcoded community data or mock data
- Use proper error handling for API calls
- Implement loading states while fetching data
- Cache API responses appropriately using React Query or similar

## Typography
- Use Poppins font family throughout the entire project
- Apply Poppins to all text elements, components, and UI elements
- Ensure consistent font usage across all pages and components
- Example: `fontFamily="'Poppins', sans-serif"`

## Code Standards
- Avoid hardcoding values unless explicitly required
- Use environment variables for API endpoints and configuration
- Extract constants to separate files or configuration objects
- Use dynamic values from props, state, or API responses
- Make components reusable and configurable through props
